> Seeing as it's Prince Harry's birthday this week, we thought we'd come up with a
> delicious British dish, which also happens (apparently) to be Prince Harry's
> favourite supper! Chicken pie is (in our opinion) the ultimate comfort food,
> so we're not surprised that this is his number one choice! Enjoy!

Put a large #pot{} of @water{2%l} on to boil with @salt{pinch}. Peel and cut the
@potato{1}(peeled into 1cm wide slices). Cut the bottom root and the top green
leafy part off the @leek{1}(cut in half lengthways), then chop into 1cm wide slices.
Chop the @celery stick{1}(chopped into roughly ½cm wide slices). Slice the
@chestnut mushrooms{1%punnet} into roughly 1cm wide slices. Chop the
@British chicken breasts{2}(cut into small bite-sized pieces). Wash your hands.

Once your water is boiling, pop in your potato slices and cook for ~{10%minutes}
or until your potato is just soft.

> Your potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through, but be careful
> because you don't want the potato slices to break up too much.

Once cooked, carefully drain your potato slices into a #colander{}.

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. While your potato is cooking, put a large
#frying pan{} on medium heat and add a @oil{drizzle}. Add your chicken, sprinkle
over @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @ground black pepper{grind} and cook for
~{5-6%minutes} until the chicken is browned and cooked through.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. You can cook your
> chicken in two batches if necessary, as you don't want to crowd the pan and
> stew the chicken, or it won't brown.

Once cooked, remove your chicken from the pan, add a drizzle more oil and then
put your leek and celery into the pan and cook for ~{4%minutes}. Once slightly
softened, add your mushrooms along with @salt{pinch} and a good grind of
@ground black pepper{grind}. Turn the heat up slightly and cook everything
together for ~{5%minutes} until the mushrooms are slightly browned.

Once your mushrooms have browned, pour in the @water{100%ml}, add the
@chicken stock pot{1}, bring to the boil and stir to dissolve. Add the
@double cream{100%ml}, bring back to the boil, turn down the heat and gently
bubble away for ~{5%minutes}, until it reduces by a third. Then, add your
chicken back into the pan.

In the meantime, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{20%g} into a #bowl{} and add
the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} and a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Stir together.

Once your creamy chicken mixture has reduced by a third, taste it and add more
@salt{} and @black pepper{} if you think it needs it. Spoon it into an
#ovenproof dish{}. Top with your slices of potato and sprinkle over your cheesy
breadcrumbs. Season with black pepper and pop on the top shelf of your oven to
cook for ~{10%minutes} (or until the top has browned).

While your pie is cooking, get your washing up done!

Once your pie has cooked, remove it from your oven and serve in #bowls{}. Voila!